title: Howard County football power rankings, seventh edition
text:
Howard County football power rankings, seventh edition Caption On the bubble Staff photo by Jen Rynda 
Centennial (0-7, Up next: at Reservoir, Oct. 23); Mt. Hebron (1-6, Up next: at Wilde Lake, Oct. 24) 
Centennial (0-7, Up next: at Reservoir, Oct. 23); Mt. Hebron (1-6, Up next: at Wilde Lake, Oct. 24) (Staff photo by Jen Rynda) Caption 10. (10) Long Reach (2-5) Photo courtesy of Jim Codespote 
Long Reach seems to have found its groove offensively, but the defense has been leaky all season as it’s averaging more than 30 points against, and the schedule isn’t doing them any favors. But the Lightning has a chance to hang around with anybody, and could beat Hammond in the season finale. (Up next: vs. Howard, Oct. 23)
